Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 06 of Thoracic CT
And I select 'Finding' radio button
When I select 'Characterization' tab is enabled
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Nodular changes' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding button' is enabled
And 'Centrilobular' radio button is enabled
And 'Perilymphatic' radio button is enabled
And 'Random distribution' radio button is enabled

And 'Miliary pattern/diffuse' radio button is enabled
And 'Peripheral' radio button is enabled
And 'Irregular/spotted' radio button is enabled

And 'Well-defined' radio button is enabled
And 'Ill-defined' radio button is enabled

And 'Micronodular' checkbox is enabled
And 'Macronodular' checkbox is enabled

And 'Ground-glass nodules' checkbox is enabled
And 'Micronodules, clusters' checkbox is enabled
And 'Reversed halo sign' checkbox is enabled
And 'Pseudoplaque' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Centrilobular' radio button
Then 'Tree-in-bud' radio button is enabled
And 'Non-tree-in-bud' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Tree-in-bud' radio button
Then 'Serial number' input field is enabled
And 'Image number' input field is enabled
And 'Import reference image' image uploader is enabled

When I select 'Macronodular' checkbox
Then 'Confluent granulomas (Sarcoid Galaxy)' checkbox is enabled
